714094f-a.title: Manhattan: 61st Street (East) - Lexington Avenue
714094f-a.text:
133 East 6lst Street, adjoining the N.W. corner of Lexington
Avenue, showing the present Junior League Building, which will by

September 2, 1928.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

714095f-a.title: Manhattan: 61st Street - Lexington Avenue
714095f-a.text:
61st Street, west from Lexington Ave., showing mainly the north
side. The large apartment houses seen are at the N.E. and N.W.
corners of Park Ave. Note the street car tracks on Lexington Ave.
which will shortly be removed; gasoline busses replacing the former
method of transportation in 1936.
April 9, 1929.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
